# Synthetic WAMIT .1 fixture for parser unit tests.
# Format: PER  I  J  A(I,J)  [B(I,J)]
#   PER == -1.0  -> infinite frequency  (only A; B not written)
#   PER == 0.0   -> zero frequency      (only A; B not written)
#   finite PER   -> A and B both given
# Periods chosen so omega = 2*pi/PER lands on exact 0.5 and 1.0 rad/s:
#   PER = 12.5663706143592   ->  omega = 0.5 rad/s
#   PER = 6.28318530717959    ->  omega = 1.0 rad/s
